FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1774019480
OL,3,CDischarging Nottingham attacks killer
OL,4,Cto GP was 'never a good plan'
OL,6,FThe triple killer was diagnosed with
OL,7,Fparanoid schizophrenia in 2020. He was
OL,8,Fdetained under mental health laws four
OL,9,Ftimes, and claimed that voices he
OL,10,Fheard got him into "trouble".
OL,12,FIn June 2023, Calocane killed
OL,13,FUniversity of Nottingham students
OL,14,FBarnaby Webber and Grace O'Malley-
OL,15,FKumar, both 19, and caretaker Ian
OL,16,FCoates, 65, before running over three
OL,17,Fpedestrians with a van.
OL,26,@rD@TOUrD@\O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/10
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1774019480
OL,3,CDischarging Nottingham attacks killer
OL,4,Cto GP was 'never a good plan'
OL,6,FDr John Milton, a consultant forensic
OL,7,Fpsychiatrist, assessed Calocane at HMP
OL,8,FManchester in August 2023 to decide
OL,9,Fwhether he should be moved to a high-
OL,10,Fsecurity hospital.
OL,12,FIn an email written by Dr Milton, he
OL,13,Fsays references to Calocane's notes
OL,14,Ffrom NHFT suggest he was discharged to
OL,15,Fhis GP "due to non-engagement".
OL,17,FHe added in the email: "Never a good
OL,18,Fplan and likely to be a criticism for
OL,19,Fthe trust to face."
OL,26,@wD@HOUwD@^O]yD@XOU{D@SO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/10
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1774019480
OL,3,CDischarging Nottingham attacks killer
OL,4,Cto GP was 'never a good plan'
OL,6,FWhen asked about this comment on
OL,7,FThursday at the inquiry in central
OL,8,FLondon, Dr Milton said: "I was just
OL,9,Frecognising someone who'd apparently
OL,10,Fhad several psychiatric admissions
OL,11,Fshouldn't be lost to follow up.
OL,13,F"There may well be a procedure where
OL,14,Fyou, after a period of non-engagement,
OL,15,Fdespite how hard you try... that may
OL,16,Fbe the reason you just have to
OL,17,Fdischarge people.
OL,26,@pD@YOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/10
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1774019480
OL,3,CDischarging Nottingham attacks killer
OL,4,Cto GP was 'never a good plan'
OL,6,F"In my experience, you would persist
OL,7,Fbecause it would be likely on the
OL,8,Fbasis of his relapsing condition that
OL,9,Fhe would have further episodes of
OL,10,Fpsychosis."
OL,12,FA statement from consultant forensic
OL,13,Fpsychiatrist Dr Kripa Ullal, who
OL,14,Fassessed Calocane's mental health on
OL,15,Fthree occasions in prison, said the
OL,16,Fkiller was "smiling incongruently" on
OL,17,Fher first visit and responded "no
OL,18,Fcomment" when asked about hearing
OL,19,Fvoices.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@KO]xD@LOUxD@bO]yD@_OUzD@HO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/10
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1774019480
OL,3,CDischarging Nottingham attacks killer
OL,4,Cto GP was 'never a good plan'
OL,6,FWriting about a separate assessment of
OL,7,FCalocane, Dr Ullal said: "I further
OL,8,Fprobed into his description of
OL,9,Fpsychosis and asked whether he had
OL,10,Fever heard voices. After thinking for
OL,11,Fa while, he acknowledged that he was
OL,12,Fhearing voices.
OL,14,F"He said he started hearing voices in
OL,15,F2020. Mainly male voices. He described
OL,16,Fhearing them all the time, including
OL,17,Fat the time of assessment.
OL,19,F"When I asked what happened when he
OL,20,Fstarted hearing voices, he stated 'got
OL,21,Finto trouble'."
OL,26,@oD@ZOUvD@AOU{D@AOU}D@OO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/10
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1774019480
OL,3,CDischarging Nottingham attacks killer
OL,4,Cto GP was 'never a good plan'
OL,6,FAmong documents found in Calocane's
OL,7,Fprison cell was a letter which said he
OL,8,Fwanted to change his legal team.
OL,10,FThe inquiry heard he wrote: "I have a
OL,11,Ffew concerns about the relationship
OL,12,Fwith the current team. The first
OL,13,Fchoice was made with limited time and
OL,14,Finformation.
OL,16,F"There have been what I thought to be
OL,17,Fcrucial periods when the team was
OL,18,Funreachable and thus we were unable to
OL,19,Fhave productive discussions about some
OL,20,Fof my concerns."
OL,26,@rD@]OUxD@AOU|D@PO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/10
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1774019480
OL,3,CDischarging Nottingham attacks killer
OL,4,Cto GP was 'never a good plan'
OL,6,FIn another six-page document, Calocane
OL,7,Fwrote about voices he could hear and
OL,8,Fthat he "became suspicious of being
OL,9,Fmonitored again".
OL,11,FA social worker at high-security
OL,12,Ffacility Rampton Hospital, in
OL,13,FNottinghamshire, Emily Doherty, said
OL,14,Fthat when she spoke to Calocane in
OL,15,FAugust 2023, he became "paranoid"
OL,16,Fbecause she had read his letters.
OL,18,FShe said: "I probed him a little bit
OL,19,Fabout some of the letters that had
OL,20,Fbeen found in his cell and his
OL,21,Fdemeanour shifted rapidly.
OL,26,@pD@IOUqD@PO]wD@XOUwD@aO]zD@KOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/10
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1774019480
OL,3,CDischarging Nottingham attacks killer
OL,4,Cto GP was 'never a good plan'
OL,6,F"He went from coming across as open,
OL,7,Fboth verbally and non-verbally, to
OL,8,Fhaving a bit more of a fixed stare. He
OL,9,Fbecame very defensive and paranoid
OL,10,Fabout me having read those letters and
OL,11,Fwho could possibly have had access to
OL,12,Fthem."
OL,14,FMs Doherty said Calocane seemed to
OL,15,F"disregard" the attacks on June 13.
OL,17,FShe said: "He didn't sort of
OL,18,Facknowledge it as being something that
OL,19,Fwas quite a serious charge against him
OL,20,Fthat could have subsequent
OL,21,Fconsequences for the rest of his life."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@FO]wD@AOUwD@KO]yD@KOU}D@gO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/10
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1774019480
OL,3,CDischarging Nottingham attacks killer
OL,4,Cto GP was 'never a good plan'
OL,6,FThe inquiry heard that Calocane's
OL,7,Fmother told Ms Doherty that he had
OL,8,Fbeen bullied at school in Portugal and
OL,9,Fthe UK when they lived in a
OL,10,F"predominantly white community".
OL,12,FThe inquiry continues.
OL,14,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,15,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,16,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,17,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,18,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,19,Fbelow...
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@_O]
